---
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
	description="ImagineMill is a free learning resource for Microsoft 365, cloud, and AI — written for the people who keep modern workplaces running."
>
	<div class="band">
		<div class="im-container im-container--md">
			<span class="im-eyebrow">About ImagineMill</span>
			<h1>Modern workplace solutions, minus the mystery</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				ImagineMill exists for one reason: the tools that run your workday shouldn't feel like a
				second job.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="im-container im-container--md">
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				Microsoft 365, the cloud, and now AI — they arrived at work faster than anyone got trained
				on them. Somewhere between "here's your login" and "we're rolling out Copilot next
				quarter," most of us were left to figure it out during lunch.
			</p>
			<p>
				We write for the people actually holding it together: the everyday user who just wants to
				share a file without triggering a permissions incident, the accidental admin who inherited
				the tenant, the manager who has to make a licensing decision by Friday. If that's you,
				welcome. You're our favorite reader.
			</p>
			<h2>How we write</h2>
			<p>
				Every article follows the same promise: <strong>hard topics, made genuinely
				understandable</strong> — without watering them down. We name the pain, explain the concept
				in plain language, then go as deep as the topic deserves. You'll leave knowing not just
				<em>what</em> to click, but <em>why</em> it works that way.
			</p>
			<p>
				No jargon left unexplained. No "simply configure the XML." No invented statistics. And
				the occasional joke, because you're reading about retention policies and you deserve one.
			</p>
			<h2>Ways to read</h2>
			<p>
				Every article is one of four types, so you always know what you're getting into:
				<a href="/categories/explainer/">explainers</a> for the concepts,
				<a href="/categories/how-to/">how-tos</a> for the hands-on work,
				<a href="/categories/decision-guide/">decision guides</a> for the "this or that?" moments,
				and <a href="/categories/strategy/">strategy</a> pieces for the people planning rollouts.
				Or just browse by <a href="/topics/">topic</a> — or hit search and type what hurts.
			</p>
			<h2>Who's behind this</h2>
			<p>
				ImagineMill is owned by <strong>PortalSpark</strong>, which offers coaching and workshops
				for teams that want hands-on help. The mill itself stays a free learning resource — that's
				the deal. If you ever want more than the articles, we're easy to find. No pressure, ever.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
	.band {
		background: var(--gradient-screen-soft);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--blue-100);
		padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-10);
	}
	.band h1 {
		margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-4);
		font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, var(--fs-display-m));
		max-width: 24ch;
	}
	.lede {
		font-size: var(--fs-body-lg);
		color: var(--text-body);
		max-width: 52ch;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.prose {
		padding: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-8);
	}
</style>
